There are several things you will need to do on the Raspberry Pi to make this work


Install node.js
Install socket.io
Install the necessary modules

//Start on Boot **(/home/pi/server.js) is path to your .js file

su pi -c 'node /home/pi/server.js < /dev/null &'

//Keep from Sleeping

Navigate to /etc/lightdm and 'sudo nano lightdm.conf' the following line under the [SeatDefaults] section
xserver-command = X -s 0 -dpms
